<HL>
   Britain's Unemployment Rate
</HL>
<DATE>
07/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   LONDON -- Unemployment in Britain rose to a provisional,
seasonally adjusted 5.7% of the work force in June, unchanged
from May, the Department of Employment estimated.
   Without seasonal adjustment, unemployment was 5.5%,
unchanged from May but down from 6.1% in June 1989. The
number of jobless people on this basis was 1,555,610 in June,
compared with 1,578,527 in May and 1,743,141 in June 1989.
</LP>
